What do you think of my new whole roasted suckling piglet 燒乳豬 cake?! I worked on the concept for a while and was inspired by my culture. In Chinese tradition, we celebrate special occasions like weddings with a whole roasted pig as a sign of prosperity! The flavours are a play  of a white forest cake pairing Roses, Sakura, Cherries, Raspberries and White chocolate together.  I tried to make the skin crispy and crunchy like a real suckling pig 🤤 

Let me know what you think and don't worry if you couldn't get your hands on one, as it will be making a come back very soon 😊 😉

🆕 🍜 🍰 👀 Slight delay in posting something I'm really excited about! Friends Christopher Siu @bakersiu and David Jorge @chefdavidjorge, former competitors turned champions from MasterChef Canada, have joined forces to bring Daan Go Cake Lab @daangocakelab to Vancouver. Originating from Toronto, where Chris has already established four successful locations, this marks their very first joint venture.

From beautifully crafted pastries like black sesame scrolls, pineapple pandan pastry, and delicious garlic cheese buns, everything is meticulously and obsessively prepared in-house. Another favourite was the black sesame and mochi cookie and the cakes are just next level and look like competition cakes off TV shows. The culinary influence at Daan Go is distinctly Asian in flavours and style and the concepts are innovative, fun and playful. Each cake is a work of art, and most importantly they go beyond just looking good. 

On the table:
1) Cheesecake Fromage - white chocolate, lime passion fruit cheesecake, citrus ganache truffle mouse
2) Ramen Bowl - pudding noodles, coffee jelly, milk chocolate mousse, chiffon cubes, caramel syrup, diced caramelized pears
3) Macaron Box 
4) Matcha scroll
5) Black sesame scroll 👍🏻
6) Pineapple pandan
7) Durian scroll
8) Garlic cheese bun 😍
9) Kaya almond scroll💫
10) Salted duck egg scroll
11) Lucky Duck - lemon curd, pistachio cream, almond sponge
12) Campfire cookie - marshmallow, graham crackers, dark chocolate chips
13) Strawberry Pocky cookie - strawberry chocolate 
14) Koala Matcha cookie - white chocolate, dark chocolate, matcha
15) Black sesame and mochi cookie 😍
16) Firma - Malted milk chocolate (Ovaltine) mousse, chocolate almond sponge, salted caramel, dark chocolate mousse, and chocolate rocks💫
17) Celebration Pig - raspberry sakura chantilly, cherry rose confit, white chocolate mousse, raspberry crunchy base
18) Gold Thorn - 100% durian purée, durian mousse, vanilla chiffon, cheese cream
19) Pandaan Cake - coconut curd, pandan chantilly, roasted pineapple confit, coconut graham base
20) Vietnamese Coffee Tiramisu - sang tao vietnamese coffee, mascarpone cream, crème légère, vanilla chiffon

Celebrating a milestone! ✨ Grateful for the incredible opportunity to share my journey in a feature on the prestigious So Good.. website. 🍰 When Daan Go started, finding my pastry style and having confidence in my technique was a struggle. And coming from a background without formal training or mentorship, self-doubt constantly lingered. Today, the fear of falling behind and the constant pursuit of new techniques persist. This feature signifies a step forward in my pastry-making journey, reassuring me that I'm on the right path. 🙌 
Thanks again @nasserb.saleh for getting me this opportunity and @angefc for always pushing me to achieve more.
#daangocakelab #bakersiu #masterchefcanada #pastrylife #sogoodmagazine #sogoodmag @sogoodmag
